B.afG=new A.c("In Plan B, White pulls the Bishop to 7c, aiming to deploy forces in the central area while applying pressure on Black's base.")
B.ajy=new A.c("In the opening stage, where to move the Bishop is very important in deciding which strategy to take. Whether your strategy is offense-oriented or defense-oriented determines where the Bishop should be placed.")
B.ajU=new A.c("Another example to show you how vital the Bishop's position can be when you are about to move into the middlegame.")
B.Ms=new A.p("ln4knl/4r1g2/p1bpsgspp/2p1ppp2/1p5P1/2PPPSP2/PPSG1PN1P/1KGB3R1/LN6L b -","Diagram 1-2")
B.ah0=new A.c("In Diagram 1-2, White has just played B7c, giving priority to defense. The Bishop here is for restricting Black's offensive formation.")
B.adA=new A.c("On the other hand, the Bishop pulled to 4b (Diagram 2-1) is for applying pressure on Black's King, therefore an offensive move.")
