B.afp=new A.c("You have nothing to worry about. When White plays S9e, you can chase it away by P9f. Also in this position, you are the one to take the initiative.")
B.adw=new A.c("Lastly, let me add the position in which you can play the edge Pawn. If White's Knight is on 7c at an early stage, as in Diagram 2-3, you can safely play P9f. In other words, as long as it's certain that White does not employ the Bo-gin, you can play P9f after White's P9d.")
B.LQ=new A.p("l6nl/1r1s1bgk1/2np1gspp/ppp1ppp2/9/2PPP1PP1/PPSG1PN1P/1KGB1S1R1/LN6L b -","Diagram 2-3")
B.amm=new A.c("This is my personal opinion, but when you play the double fortress opening, it is better to play something for the future offense rather than playing the defensive move (P9f in response to P9d).")
B.a1N=A.a(s([B.akj,B.a9O,B.Oi,B.ae_,B.aiM,B.a9u,B.Lp,B.afp,B.adw,B.LQ,B.amm]),t.A)
B.ac7=new A.ap(B.a1N)
