B.acM=new A.ap(B.ZV)
B.alN=new A.c("A vanguard Pawn is a pretty good thing to have, from which you can build up your future strategy, but it could work against you at times.")
B.NE=new A.p("lnsgkg1nl/1r5b1/ppppps1pp/5pp2/4P4/2P3PP1/PP1P1P2P/1B3S1R1/LNSGKG1NL w -","Diagram 2-1")
B.aiq=new A.c("In Diagram 2-1, Black has just played to make the midfile-Pawn into a vanguard (P5e), but it was a bad idea.")
B.S5=A.a(s(["R5b","S5g","P5d","Px5d","Sx5d"]),t.s)
B.a9l=new A.P("After Diagram 2-1:",B.S5,B.r)
B.KN=new A.p("lnsgkg1nl/4r2b1/pppp3pp/4spp2/9/2P3PP1/PP1PSP2P/1B5R1/LNSGKG1NL b Pp","Diagram 2-2")
B.afZ=new A.c("Above is a typical example where White's counterattack worked. Black should have known his S5g was too late to support the Pawn on 5e.")
B.ady=new A.c("Diagram 2-3 (last move P8e) is another illustration of an attempted vanguard Pawn from a Yagura opening.")
B.LX=new A.p("ln4knl/1r1s2g2/p2p1gspp/2pbppp2/1p7/2PPP1P2/PPSG1PSPP/1KGB3R1/LN5NL b -","Diagram 2-3")
