B.afj=new A.c("In response to the third move, P-5e, White didn't play S-4c. If he had, Black's R-2f would have been just the right defense. If White had played Bx6f+, Black would have responded with B-7g, which would make a great difference compared with a position where Black played R-2f in the first place.")
B.ajI=new A.c("Diagram 2-3 shows both parties in equilibrium. Compare it with Diagram 2-1 where Black's Rook and Gold are forked, which you might well consider a crisis. Black played deftly, put the proverb into practice and got himself out of trouble.")
